sentences: Keith Alan Lockhart (born November 7, 1959) is an American conductor.

Born on November 7, 1959, in Poughkeepsie, New York, Lockhart is the elder of two children, (the younger being Paul D. Lockhart) born to Newton Frederick and Marilyn Jean (Woodyard) Lockhart, who worked as computer professionals.
Lockhart graduated in 1981 from Furman University with a double major in German and piano performance.
Lockhart was initiated into Phi Mu Alpha Sinfonia fraternity in 1978 by the Gamma Eta chapter at Furman University.
